init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It looks like it was written by a first grader.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're eating a piece of toast when you hear the doorbell ring.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It's a man in a black suit.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm here to help you pack," he says.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: two men in black suits, and they don't look amused.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Mister Obama, I'm going to have to ask you to come with us."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "We're here to take you to meet with JFK," says one of the black suited figures.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: there's a rustling in the bushes.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Mister Obama, you should come with us."
